body:
two kinds of people-

group one: never really cared for Reed- and definitely not Lester- to begin with. They think of him only as a plot device to cause Tyrus angst, and tell a message that needs to be spoken (so basically what the writers intended people to do)

the second group: Reed and Lester are our babies okay? Reed’s a dumbass but deserves our love, and just because Lester does not speak, does not mean Lester is of any less value. Our babies deserve all of the love in the world. (this is me)

summary: So I translated the swing scene to Hebrew, retranslated it to English, back to Hebrew and once again back to English. This is...
body:
So I translated the swing scene to Hebrew, retranslated it to English, back to Hebrew and once again back to English. This is the unedited result.

Cyrus: “Legs rise, legs come down, that’s how we make the swing, take your feet, you walk slowly as you drag, you go less - legs go up -

Tj: "Nice song.

What are you singing on the slide? ”

“We go down, we say” yay “we do not climb up, it’s not true.”

“You did not expect to have a song.”

“Chips chocolate muffin chocolate, right?”

“Scary basketball man”.

“Actually, T.J.”

“I know.

Cyrus. ”

“So, are you hanging around here a lot?”

“Only when I feel bad about myself.

So quite often. ”

“Hmmm.

Does it help? ”

“It helps me.

Come on, you look like you need it. ”

“(SIGHS) Wow, it makes me feel a bit better.”

“What should you feel better than you are the captain of the basketball team.”

“You do not know me.

I have things. ”

“I must have other things.”

“Yeah, I bet I can swing higher.”

“I’m afraid to become tall.

That’s part of my stuff. ”

(Czech Republic) Wu, I do not know why I ever stopped rocking! (Laughter) Come on, get up, it’s like I’m going. “

"Wo! (Chuckles) Wah!

"Underdog!”

“Oh, wow.”

“It was exciting!”

“Do you want another one?”

“No thanks.”

“Hmm, sorry”
